"a.虚幻的 【英】 adj. 虚幻的(deceptive; unreal; illusive) 【考】 maelstrom : turbulent / mirage : illusory(大旋涡的特点是汹涌 的/海市蜃楼的特点是 虚幻的) 【记】 来自 illusion(幻觉), il+lus(玩弄)→被玩 弄→错觉 adj. 虚幻的; 幻觉的 = deceptive = illusive 【类】maelstrom: turbulent = mirage: illusory大旋涡是汹涌的 = 海市蜃楼是虚幻的 【记】il 假的，坏的，病的+ lusion 感觉，印象 illusory (adj.)  1590s, from French illusorie, from Late Latin illusorius ""ironical, of a mocking character,"" from illus-, past participle stem of Latin illudere ""mock at,"" literally ""to play with,"" from assimilated form of in- ""at, upon"" (see in- (2)) + ludere ""to play"" (see ludicrous)."
